        <div type="letter">
         <opener><dateline><date when="1917-07-11">August 9, 1917.<dateline></date><salute>Dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet</persName>:-</salute>
        </opener>
            <p>
            <!-- The value of the currency is 100 dollars. The money was sent in HMonroe1917-10-04 -->
                I am sorry I sent the <measure type="currency" num="100">money</measure> too soon, but you can easily guard it in your private account until you need it. The truth was I mistook a month — I don’t know why — and when I wrote you thought it was the first of September, but it won’t make any difference in the long run.
                Will you be an angel and send me a proof of my article on <persName key="eunice_tietjens">Eunice Tietjens</persName>? You know I like to correct my own proofs.
            </p>
                <closer>Affectionately yours,</closer>
           
